                            <p>
                                Figure 8: Gel batteries
                            </p>
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <p>Gel Batteries: A gel battery (also known as a “gel cell”) is a sealed, valve regulated lead-acid deep cycle battery and has a gel electrolyte. Unlike flooded lead-acid (wet cell) batteries, these batteries do not need to be kept upright.</p>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td colspan="2">Common brands Include: Deka, Champion, Sonnenschein, Victron, Trojan</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>
